==== File extensions and major mode selection ====

Downloading the zip and following the instructions works for me, except they seem to suggest that after you run autostart.el, every time you start emacs with an "example .html" extension, that would somehow load the file and set the right mode. This is simply not the case in my experience. However adding this at the end worked:

{{{
(load "nxhtml/autostart.el")
(add-to-list 'auto-mode-alist '("\\.html$" . nxhtml-mode))
(add-to-list 'auto-mode-alist '("\\.shtml$" . nxhtml-mode))
(add-to-list 'auto-mode-alist '("\\.htm$" . nxhtml-mode))
}}}

I wish the instructions were a bit clearer..
[new] You and me both :(

[new]
And I would like a bug report to understand where the problem is... ;-)

